% 1
[V: S1V1] [Q:1/4=100]  F3/2 F/ F F | E F G2 | G G G G | F G A2 |
w: 1.~Now the light has gone a- way; Fa- ther, lis- ten while I pray, 
w: 2.~Je- sus, Sa- vior, wash a- way All that has been wrong to- day; 
w: 3.~Let my near and dear ones be Al- ways near and dear to Thee. 
w: 4.~Now my eve- ning praise I give; Thou didst die that I might live. 
w: 5.~Thou, my best and kind- est Friend, Thou wilt love me to the end. 
[V: S1V2]  C3/2 C/ C C | C C E2 | E E E E | F E F2 |
[V: S2V1]  A,3/2 A,/ A, C | B, A, C2 | C C C C | C C C2 |
[V: S2V2]  F,3/2 F,/ F, A, | G, F, C,2 | C, C, C, B, | A, G, F,2 |
% 5
[V: S1V1]  A3/2 A/ A A | G F d2 | !sintro!c A c B | D E F2 !eintro!|]
w: Ask- ing Thee to watch and keep And to send me qui- et sleep. 
w: Help me ev- ery day to be Good and gen- tle, more like Thee. 
w: Oh, bring me and all I love To Thy ha- ppy home a- bove. 
w: All my bless- ings come from Thee; Oh, how good Thou art to me! 
w: Let me love Thee more and more, Al- ways bet- ter than be- fore. 
[V: S1V2]  F F F F | E _E D2 | F F F F | D C C2 |]
[V: S2V1]  C C C C | B, A, [F,2B,2] | A, C A, D | B, B, A,2 |]
